    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.15.13-14_0002" />
                <fw type="curatorial">14</fw>
                
                <fw type="imprint">
                    ST. LOUIS POST-DIPSATCH
                    <lb/>
                    "Of Making Many Books"
                    <lb/>
                    JOHN G. NEIHARDT
                    <lb/>
                    BRANSON, MISSOURI
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
        <dateline>Jan 10 '31</dateline>
                
                <salute>Dear Comrade:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Yes, another birthday &#8212; 50 of them so far! As for "whopping sunsets", the stuff of <hi rend="italic">ours</hi> is already in existence, and nothing but a bit of <hi rend="italic">obvious</hi> lying is needed to prove it. Not that I give a damn, but it's so. I have more power &#8212; or rather have access to greater sources of power &#8212; than ever before; and care less to use it than ever. But, being here, one might as well let loose. I suppose; though I'm a bit fed up on kindergarten stuff &amp; should be glad to try the first grade somewhere or other. If <hi rend="italic">this</hi> were all, then, obscene Rabelaisian laughter <del/> would be the most pertinent comment; and when I say this I mean something very definite that I could work out convincingly a few hours of conversation. But, this <hi rend="italic">isn't</hi> all. That's the only reason I'm at all willing to stay &amp; fool around Our whole social structure is too funny for the most abandoned ribaldry to express; but there are fine spirits imprisoned here. We will live on for them, humbly, hoping to help.</p> <closer><salute>Endless love, Comrade.</salute> <signed>Jno.</signed></closer>
                
                <note type="authorial">I do love you. It is far more than a mere expression of friendly feeling &#8212; you are a good spirit.</note>
                
                
            </div1>
            
            
            
